<title>ScottOS Privacy Policy</title>
<h1>ScottOS Privacy Policy</h1>
<p><strong>Effective:</strong> August 2025</p>
<p>ScottOS sends calendar action requests (e.g., create/update/delete events) to this API. Google OAuth tokens are stored server-side and never shared with ChatGPT. No chat history is stored by this API.</p>
<h2>What We Store</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Google OAuth tokens to access your Google Calendar on your behalf.</li>
  <li>Event data you explicitly ask us to create or modify via the API.</li>
</ul>
<h2>What We Donâ€™t Store</h2>
<ul>
  <li>No chat logs or conversation data from ChatGPT.</li>
  <li>No sale or sharing of your data with third parties.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Security</h2>
<ul>
  <li>API requests require a secret key and are served over HTTPS.</li>
  <li>Tokens are stored server-side only.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Revocation & Deletion</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Revoke access anytime via your Google Account &rarr; Security &rarr; Third-party access.</li>
  <li>Contact: you@example.com for removal requests or questions.</li>
</ul>
